    "Another interesting source is Mahela et al. (2019)-this work provides a comprehensive review of Low Voltage Ride-Through (LVRT) techniques that are essential for maintaining the connection of wind turbines during voltage fluctuations; hence, this study is very important for grid code compliance.",
    "Two of the most common sources used in the analysis are textbooks Abad et al. (2011) and Wu et al.",
    "( 2011) that give detailed information about the DFIG modelling and control, information which is crucial for both theoretical and practical professions.",
    "A comprehensive work on wind power systems was presented by Ackermann (2005) with a focus on wind power integration into electrical grid.",
    "Altogether, these articles build a strong groundwork for further developments in the control of the DFIG-based wind turbines which shows both theoretical contributions and application-oriented works in the domain of wind energy.Table 4 presents a detailed analysis of various clusters related to WECS."
